uniqueIssues.suggestedFix:
Remove the global outline reset and provide visible focus styles for interactive elements.
Example:
/* Remove this rule entirely */
/* * { outline: none !important; } */

/* Provide accessible focus styles */
:focus-visible { outline: 3px solid #1a1a1a; outline-offset: 3px; }
.btn:focus-visible, a:focus-visible, .book-btn:focus-visible { outline: 3px solid #c9a962; outline-offset: 3px; }

Keep a non-color visual indicator for links (e.g., underline), and ensure sufficient contrast from body text.
Example:
a { color: #0a66c2; text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px; }
a:hover { text-decoration-thickness: 2px; }
/* If you must remove underlines in some contexts, add another non-color cue like a border, icon, or font-weight change while maintaining contrast. */

Use a text color that achieves at least 4.5:1 contrast against the background (or 3:1 for large text). For example:
:root { --text-low-contrast: #6b7280; /* or use var(--text-dark) */ }
.low-contrast-text { color: var(--text-dark); }

Provide a non-color cue and/or text label with the status dot. For example, add visible text or an icon shape difference and include accessible names:
/* CSS (supplemental visual cue) */
.status-available { background-color: #22c55e; border: 2px solid #1a1a1a; }
.status-booked { background-color: #ef4444; border: 2px dashed #1a1a1a; }
/* Also include adjacent text like “Available”/“Booked” or add visually hidden text: */
.visually-hidden { position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; padding: 0; margin: -1px; overflow: hidden; clip: rect(0 0 0 0); white-space: nowrap; border: 0; }

Provide a non-color cue and/or text label with the status dot. For example, add visible text or an icon shape difference and include accessible names:
/* CSS (supplemental visual cue) */
.status-available { background-color: #22c55e; border: 2px solid #1a1a1a; }
.status-booked { background-color: #ef4444; border: 2px dashed #1a1a1a; }
/* Also include adjacent text like “Available”/“Booked” or add visually hidden text: */
.visually-hidden { position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; padding: 0; margin: -1px; overflow: hidden; clip: rect(0 0 0 0); white-space: nowrap; border: 0; }

Use a darker color that achieves at least 4.5:1 contrast against white, or increase the text to large size with sufficient weight and still meet 3:1.
Example fix:
.price-table td:not(:first-child) { color: #705327; /* or use var(--primary-dark) */ }

Retain a non-color visual indicator for links and ensure adequate contrast.
Example:
.price-note a { text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px; color: #0a66c2; }

Use a darker color that meets at least 4.5:1 against #faf9f7, or increase the text size/weight to qualify as large text while still meeting 3:1.
Example:
.section-label { color: #705327; /* or var(--primary-dark) */ }

Use a darker color for prices that achieves at least 3:1 contrast with white.
Example:
.room-price { color: #705327; /* darker gold */ }

Use a hover color with sufficient contrast and/or add a non-color cue (underline, background change).
Example:
.room-link:hover { color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px; }

